claim.claim-text:
1. A method of cleaning a drive chain or belt comprising the steps of coiling a strip brush having a base and projecting filaments to form a helix with the filaments directing inwardly to form an inverted coil brush,
placing the brush beside a drive chain or belt;
rotating the brush to thread it on to the drive chain or belt until the brush completely surrounds the drive chain or belt;
relatively moving the brush and drive chain or belt to clean the drive chain or belt; and
then removing the brush by unthreading it from the chain or belt by rotating the helix.
